ith `owner_group` in the same sorted order, and **every** task has truthy `title`, `due_at`, and `status === \"open\"`.\n  - `customer_messages` has a row with matching `request_id` and truthy `body`.\n  - `audit_events` has a row with matching `request_id` and truthy `customer_visible`.\n\nCritical detail: `after` is the return value of `applyBenchmarkTask` AND the test re-reads `runData` for persistence. So `applyBenchmarkTask` must **mutate `db` in place** (push rows into the empty arrays) **and** return `buildPortalView(db)` reflecting that state.\n\n## 5. Schema / migration (full) — `migrations/001_table_contract.sql`\nPostgres DDL with all columns typed `text`. Note: this DDL is a \"contract\" artifact only — **there is no live Postgres connection anywhere in the code/tests.** The \"database\" is the in-memory `tables.json` object. The four output tables are declared with a single scalar `value` column in SQL, but in the JSON fixture they are plain empty arrays expecting object rows:\n- `benchmark_fixture`, `accounts`, `account_contracts`, `contacts`, `workflow_requests`, `workflow_request_owner_groups`, `workflow_request_risk_signals`, `activities` — input tables.\n- `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages` — output tables (start empty).\n\n## 6. Fixture data — `data/tables.json` (161 lines, 4902 bytes)\nStructure (all arrays of flat objects):\n- `benchmark_fixture` (1), `accounts` (1: `acct-invoice-di`), `account_contracts` (1, platinum/$72k ARR), `contacts` (2: Operations + Finance).\n- `workflow_requests` (1): `request_id: \"invoice-invoice-disp\"`, `task_id: \"invoice-dispute-workflow\"`, `primary_entity: \"invoice\"`, `expected_outcome` = exactly the expected status string, `next_step: \"Finance owner review by 16:00\"`, `customer_message: \"Invoice dispute workflow is being handled by Finance, Customer Success, Legal, Operations.\"`.\n- `workflow_request_owner_groups` (4): Finance(1), Customer Success(2), Legal(3), Operations